quran[30]{c,v,t,f}:
  74,37,"To whoever wills among you to proceed{1} or stay behind.",1:[To righteousness by acceptance of the warning.]
  74,38,"Every soul, for what it has earned, will be retained{1}.",1:[i.e., subject or held responsible.]
  74,39,"Except the companions of the right,{1}.",1:[i.e., the righteous who receive their records in their right hands.]
  75,34,"Woe to you, and woe!"
  75,35,"Then woe to you, and woe!"
  75,36,"Does man think that he will be left neglected?{1}",1:[i.e., to no end, without responsibility, or without being returned to the Creator for judgement.]
  76,28,"We have created them and strengthened their forms, and when We will, We can change their likenesses with [complete] alteration."
  76,29,"Indeed, this is a reminder, so he who wills may take to his Lord a way."
  76,30,"And you do not will except that Allāh wills. Indeed, Allāh is ever Knowing and Wise."
  77,25,"Have We not made the earth a container"
  77,26,"Of the living and the dead?"
  77,27,"And We placed therein lofty, firmly set mountains and have given you to drink sweet water."
  78,22,"For the transgressors, a place of return,"
  78,23,"In which they will remain for ages [unending]."
  78,24,"They will not taste therein [any] coolness or drink."
  79,16,"When his Lord called to him in the sacred valley of Ṭuwā,"
  79,17,""
  79,18,"And say to him, 'Would you [be willing to] purify yourself"
  80,13,"[It is recorded] in honored sheets,"
  80,14,"Exalted and purified,"
  80,15,"[Carried] by the hands of messenger-angels,"
  81,10,"And when the pages{1} are spread [i.e., made public]",1:[On which are recorded the deeds of all people.]
  81,11,"And when the sky is stripped away"
  81,12,"And when Hellfire is set ablaze"
  82,4,"And when the [contents of] graves are scattered [i.e., exposed],"
  82,5,"A soul will [then] know what it has put forth and kept back."
  82,6,"O mankind, what has deceived you concerning your Lord, the Generous,"
  83,1,"Woe to those who give less [than due],{1}",1:[i.e., those who cheat people by giving them less than what they paid for when weighing or measuring - an amount so little as to hardly be noticed.]
  83,2,"Who, when they take a measure from people, take in full."
  83,3,"But if they give by measure or by weight to them, they cause loss."